Package: gnome-remote-desktop-gdm-hwenc
Version: 1.0
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
Depends: acl
Enhances: gnome-remote-desktop
Description: hardware-accelerated encode for the GDM login screen (Rockchip)
 gnome-remote-desktop hardware-encodes the RDP stream on Rockchip via the MPP
 video codec. The base codec udev rule grants the "video" group access, which
 covers the interactive login user but NOT the GDM greeter: the greeter runs as
 a dynamic per-session user (gdm-greeter, gdm-greeter-2, ...) that is only ever
 in group "gdm". This package grants the "gdm" group a persistent ACL on the
 codec nodes (/dev/mpp_service, the DMA-heaps, /dev/rga) so the login screen is
 hardware-encoded too, not just the logged-in session.
 .
 Separate / opt-in: it widens video-codec access to the whole "gdm" group, so it
 is deliberately not pulled in by gnome-remote-desktop.
